  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving access to life saving response to cyclone affected women, men, boys and girls in lughaya district Awdal region of Somaliland through restocking and unconditional cash transfer</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to improve immediate food access by increasing the purchasing power of the beneficiaries through unconditional cash grants(cash+) as well as restocking of the vulnerable Households (goats 9 female and one male) affected by cycle Sigar since they lost up to 70 per cent of their livestock and are at risk of slipping to crisis (IPC 3). The project targets, selection and registration will be community based and women and minorities who filled the criteria will be given priority. The project entails three components: unconditional cash grant 
The unconditional cash grant will target 350 households for four (4) months with full MEB in Lugahaya districts, Restocking of 150 HH for the families(among the unconditional target vulnerable HHs) that lost their livestock and willing to resume their nomad life with 10 heads of goats (9 lactating and one male) and providing supplements blocks 10 KG per HH, vaccinate against PPR/SGP and deworm to restocking targeted beneficiaries</narrative>
  </description>
